content: OK.  Just spent (way) too long on the phone with someone who isn’t going to vote but every issue he brought up was pro Harris and anti Trump.  I wanted to send him the kamalaharris.com link but wasn’t given the opportunity in the dialer.  I tagged him “not voting” and then “undecided” on the next screen, but it didn’t give me a link to provide additional information.  Did I miss something?

Some scripts have a link to text, others do not.  Your selections are right and in this case it would be up to him to visit the issues page on his own.  I hope your conversation convinced him to reconsider not voting.  Its mindboggling right?

COMPLETELY!  His biggest concern was that the government makes decisions without input from the electorate!  And he mentioned the 1%ers and homelessness, etc.  I'm so worried for this country!  Thanks Denise!!!  Back to calling and texting...
